<subSubSection id="A58A652EFFFBFFE1DFA2FF2AFB3B97B8" pageId="1" pageNumber="276" type="key">
<keyStep id="56642E00FFFBFFE1DFA2FF2AFB3A9718" pageId="1" pageNumber="276">
<paragraph id="ED2F36A5FFFBFFE1DFA2FF2AFB3A9752" blockId="1.[174,1233,218,480]" pageId="1" pageNumber="276">
<keyLead id="56619590FFFBFFE1DFA2FF2AFB3A9752" pageId="1" pageNumber="276">
1. Arista thickened in basal third of last aristomere with dense black hairs (
<figureCitation id="75AB2A20FFFBFFE1DCAFFF2AFC3F96A8" box="[931,981,218,240]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,852,874]" captionTargetBox="[241,1143,176,830]" captionTargetId="figure-6@3.[232,1200,147,837]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 6–8. Chyliza qaradaghi, sp. n., holotype ♀: 6 — left wing, 7 — pattern of hind leg, 8 — antenna, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453154" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453154/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="276">fig. 8</figureCitation>
) Male fore tibiae without anteroventral comb of black spinules. ................................................................................Subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="2A904D26FFFBFFE1DB6DFF05FB439752" authorityName="Robineau-Desvoidy" authorityYear="1830" box="[1121,1193,245,266]" class="Insecta" family="Psilidae" genus="Chyliza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="276" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Dasyna">
<emphasis id="DFE4EAB7FFFBFFE1DB6DFF05FB439752" box="[1121,1193,245,266]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="276">Dasyna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(2)
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ED2F36A5FFFBFFE1DFA2FEFFFB3A9718" blockId="1.[174,1233,218,480]" pageId="1" pageNumber="276">
<keyLead id="56619590FFFBFFE1DFA2FEFFFB3A9718" pageId="1" pageNumber="276">
— Arista slender. Male fore tibiae with anteroventral comb of black spinules in basal third or half. ………… ............................................................................................................................................ Subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="2A904D26FFFBFFE1DB44FEDAFB3A9718" authority="Fallen" authorityName="Fallen" authorityYear="1820" box="[1096,1232,298,320]" class="Insecta" family="Psilidae" genus="Chyliza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="276" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DFE4EAB7FFFBFFE1DB44FEDAFB7A9718" box="[1096,1168,298,320]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="276">Chyliza</emphasis>
Fallen
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="56642E00FFFBFFE1DFA2FEB4FB3B97B8" pageId="1" pageNumber="276">
<paragraph id="ED2F36A5FFFBFFE1DFA2FEB4FB3A97C8" blockId="1.[174,1233,218,480]" pageId="1" pageNumber="276">
<keyLead id="56619590FFFBFFE1DFA2FEB4FB3A97C8" pageId="1" pageNumber="276">
2. Head mainly yellow, only occiput partly black (
<figureCitation id="75AB2A20FFFBFFE1DDAFFEB4FD079702" box="[675,749,324,346]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[173,206,1104,1126]" captionTargetBox="[223,1152,174,1092]" captionTargetId="figure-315@2.[229,1155,603,1103]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 2–5. Chyliza qaradaghi sp. n., head: 2, 3 — female (2 — lateral view, 3 — dorsal view), 4, 5 — male (4 — lateral view, 5 — dorsal view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453152" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453152/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="276">fig. 2–5</figureCitation>
); antennal postpedicel 2 times longer than high at base, hind tibia with large lateral black area on 2/3 apical part (
<figureCitation id="75AB2A20FFFBFFE1DC3FFEAFFC8F972D" box="[819,869,351,373]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,852,874]" captionTargetBox="[241,1143,176,830]" captionTargetId="figure-6@3.[232,1200,147,837]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 6–8. Chyliza qaradaghi, sp. n., holotype ♀: 6 — left wing, 7 — pattern of hind leg, 8 — antenna, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453154" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453154/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="276">fig. 7</figureCitation>
), 
<quantity id="2A689B40FFFBFFE1DC7AFEAFFC33972D" box="[886,985,351,373]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.75" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="276" unit="mm" value="4.75" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.5">4.5–5 mm</quantity>
, from 
<collectingCountry id="95877635FFFBFFE1DB14FEAFFBA9972D" box="[1048,1091,351,373]" name="Iran" pageId="1" pageNumber="276">Iran</collectingCountry>
. ........................ ................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="2A904D26FFFBFFE1DC0EFE8AFB3A97C8" authority="Khaghaninia et Gharajedaghi" authorityName="Khaghaninia et Gharajedaghi" authorityYear="2014" box="[770,1232,378,400]" class="Insecta" family="Psilidae" genus="Chyliza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="276" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="qaradaghi">
<emphasis id="DFE4EAB7FFFBFFE1DC0EFE8AFC5B97C8" box="[770,945,378,400]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="276">Chyliza qaradaghi</emphasis>
Khaghaninia et Gharajedaghi
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ED2F36A5FFFBFFE1DFA2FE64FB3B97B8" blockId="1.[174,1233,218,480]" pageId="1" pageNumber="276">
<keyLead id="56619590FFFBFFE1DFA2FE64FB3B97B8" pageId="1" pageNumber="276">
— Head completely black (
<figureCitation id="75AB2A20FFFBFFE1DEB3FE64FE1697F2" box="[447,508,404,426]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[170,203,896,918]" captionTargetBox="[259,1061,199,868]" captionTargetId="figure-345@4.[243,1113,174,895]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 12–15. Chyliza extenuata, ♀: 12 — total view, left; 13 — head, lateral view; 14 — hypopigium, dorsal view; 15 — aedeagus. Scale bar 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453158" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453158/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="276">fig. 13</figureCitation>
), antennal postpedicel more than 2 times longer than high at base, hind tibia without black area, 
<quantity id="2A689B40FFFBFFE1DE9BFE5FFE10979D" box="[407,506,431,453]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.25" metricValueMax="5.5" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="276" unit="mm" value="5.25" valueMax="5.5" valueMin="5.0">5–5.5 mm</quantity>
, from Europe, Middle East and 
<collectingCountry id="95877635FFFBFFE1DC21FE5FFC53979D" box="[813,953,431,453]" name="Turkmenistan" pageId="1" pageNumber="276">Turkmenistan</collectingCountry>
. ................................………… ........................................................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="2A904D26FFFBFFE1DCD7FE3AFB3B97B8" authority="(Rossi)" baseAuthorityName="Rossi" baseAuthorityYear="1790" box="[987,1233,458,480]" class="Insecta" family="Psilidae" genus="Chyliza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="276" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="extenuata">
<emphasis id="DFE4EAB7FFFBFFE1DCD7FE3AFB6D9787" box="[987,1159,458,480]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="276">Chyliza extenuata</emphasis>
(Rossi)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
